list.title: SDKInstanceBase
list.description: The SDKInstanceBase interface is used as the base class for runtime instances in the SDK. For "world" type plugins, instances instead derive from SDKWorldInstanceBase which itself derives from SDKInstanceBase.

list.title: SDKPluginBase
list.description: The SDKPluginBase interface is used as the base class for your plugin in the runtime.

list.title: SDKTypeBase
list.description: The SDKTypeBase interface is used as the base class for runtime object types in the SDK. An object type corresponds to an object listed in the Project Bar. Object types may have multiple instances.

list.title: IInstanceBase
list.description: The IInstanceBase interface is used as the base class for instances in the SDK. For "world" type plugins, instances instead derive from IWorldInstanceBase, which itself derives from IInstanceBase.

list.title: IPluginBase
list.description: The main configuration for a plugin.

list.title: ITypeBase
list.description: Plugin type definition in editor. It is constant class, follow API example.
